        <abstract> 
<p>CW’s article responding to Mivart [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">8351</hi>] on the fixity of species is very clear.</p> 
            <p>On evolution of language, CD doubts W. D. Whitney’s claim that changes are effected by the will of man. Asks CW when a thing may properly be said to be so effected.</p>
        </abstract>
